<% content_for :title, "Help" %>

<div class="max-w-3xl">
  <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-stone-900 mb-2">Help</h1>
  <p class="text-sm text-stone-500 mb-10">
    Common workflows and what the icons mean. If something isn't covered
    here, ask Mike — he's the one to bug.
  </p>

  <%# Adding a book %>
  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-stone-900 mb-3">Adding a book to your library</h2>
    <p class="text-stone-700 mb-4">
      Tsundoku doesn't host books on its own — it picks up EPUB files
      from a shared "ingest" folder. The easy path is through
      <strong>Shelfmark</strong>, which talks to the same folder.
    </p>

    <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 space-y-2 text-stone-700 mb-4">
      <li>Open a list (Lists tab in the navbar). Books not yet in your library show <span class="text-stone-500">Not in library</span> next to them with a <span class="text-amber-700 font-medium">Find on Shelfmark</span> link.</li>
      <li>Click <strong>Find on Shelfmark</strong>. Shelfmark opens with the book's title and author already filled in.</li>
      <li>Pick the right edition from Shelfmark's results and click its <strong>Download</strong> button.</li>
      <li>That's it. Within about two minutes, Tsundoku finds the file and adds the book to your library.</li>
    </ol>

    <p class="text-stone-700">
      If the book had an ISBN in its file, Tsundoku will also fetch the
      cover and description from <a href="https://hardcover.app" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-amber-700 underline hover:text-amber-800">Hardcover</a>.
      You'll see a notification at the top of the page asking you to
      review the suggestions — click <strong>Review</strong> to accept
      or reject each piece. (You can ignore the review; it'll fade on
      its own.)
    </p>
  </section>

  <%# Getting books onto the Kobo %>
  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-stone-900 mb-3">Getting books onto your Kobo</h2>
    <p class="text-stone-700 mb-4">
      Every book on your Kobo gets there through a <strong>shelf</strong>.
      The fastest way is the <span class="text-amber-700 font-medium">star</span>
      in the top-left of any book cover — one tap and the book lands on
      your <strong>Starred</strong> shelf, which is set to sync to the
      Kobo by default.
    </p>

    <p class="text-stone-700 mb-4">
      For more organization (e.g., a "Currently re-reading" or "Holiday
      reading" group), create a regular shelf and turn its <strong>Sync
      to Kobo</strong> toggle on. Click the <span class="text-amber-700 font-medium">+</span>
      in the top-right of a book cover to add the book to that shelf.
    </p>

    <p class="text-stone-700 mb-3">
      The difference between the two:
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1 text-stone-700 mb-4">
      <li><strong>Starred</strong> books sync to the Kobo but don't show up as a separate collection on the device — the Kobo's "My Books" view already covers "everything that's on here."</li>
      <li><strong>Custom syncing shelves</strong> show up on the Kobo as named collections — books on "Holiday reading" appear in a "Holiday reading" collection on the device.</li>
    </ul>

    <p class="text-stone-700">
      Either way, books show up on your Kobo the next time the device
      checks in (automatic when it has Wi-Fi). No <strong>Sync now</strong>
      button on Tsundoku — the Kobo does the asking.
    </p>
  </section>

  <%# About that "syncs" label %>
  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-stone-900 mb-3">The "syncs" label isn't a button</h2>
    <p class="text-stone-700 mb-3">
      When you open the + shelf picker on a book and see <strong class="text-blue-700 uppercase text-xs tracking-wide">syncs</strong>
      next to a shelf name, that's a <em>label</em>, not a button. It just
      tells you "this shelf is set to sync to the Kobo." You don't have
      to click it.
    </p>
    <p class="text-stone-700">
      To turn syncing on or off for a whole shelf, open the shelf itself
      and flip its <strong>Sync to Kobo</strong> toggle there. The
      Starred shelf is the one exception — its sync can't be turned
      off, because the star icon depends on it.
    </p>
  </section>

  <%# What the colors and icons mean %>
  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-stone-900 mb-3">What the colors and icons mean</h2>
    <dl class="space-y-3 text-stone-700">
      <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
        <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-amber-500 text-white shadow-sm" aria-hidden="true">
          <svg class="w-3.5 h-3.5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path d="M12 2l2.998 6.97L22 9.97l-5.5 5.06L18 22l-6-3.7L6 22l1.5-6.97L2 9.97l7.002-1.0L12 2z"/>
          </svg>
        </span>
        <div>
          <dt class="font-semibold text-stone-900">Filled amber star (top-left of a book cover)</dt>
          <dd class="text-sm">This book is on your Starred shelf — it'll sync to your Kobo. Tap to remove.</dd>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
        <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-white border border-stone-300 text-stone-500 shadow-sm" aria-hidden="true">
          <svg class="w-3.5 h-3.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 2l2.998 6.97L22 9.97l-5.5 5.06L18 22l-6-3.7L6 22l1.5-6.97L2 9.97l7.002-1.0L12 2z"/>
          </svg>
        </span>
        <div>
          <dt class="font-semibold text-stone-900">Outline star (top-left of a book cover)</dt>
          <dd class="text-sm">This book isn't on the Starred shelf yet. Tap to add — it'll sync to your Kobo on the next sync.</dd>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
        <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-amber-600 text-white shadow-sm" aria-hidden="true">
          <svg class="w-3 h-3" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2.5" d="M12 4v16m8-8H4"/>
          </svg>
        </span>
        <div>
          <dt class="font-semibold text-stone-900">Amber + (top-right of a book cover)</dt>
          <dd class="text-sm">This book is on at least one of your shelves. Click to manage all shelf memberships (including Starred).</dd>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
        <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-white border border-stone-300 text-stone-600 shadow-sm" aria-hidden="true">
          <svg class="w-3 h-3" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2.5" d="M12 4v16m8-8H4"/>
          </svg>
        </span>
        <div>
          <dt class="font-semibold text-stone-900">White + (top-right of a book cover)</dt>
          <dd class="text-sm">This book isn't on any shelf yet. Click to open the picker and add it to one.</dd>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
        <span class="shrink-0 inline-flex items-center justify-center min-w-[1.5rem] px-1.5 text-xs rounded-full bg-amber-100 text-amber-800 font-medium" aria-hidden="true">3</span>
        <div>
          <dt class="font-semibold text-stone-900">"On your Kobo" pill in the navbar</dt>
          <dd class="text-sm">How many books are currently flagged for your Kobo — books on the Starred shelf plus any custom syncing shelves.</dd>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
        <span class="shrink-0 inline-flex items-center justify-center w-6 h-6 text-blue-600" aria-hidden="true">
          <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2.5" d="M3 12l3-3m0 0l3 3m-3-3v12M21 12l-3 3m0 0l-3-3m3 3V3"/>
          </svg>
        </span>
        <div>
          <dt class="font-semibold text-stone-900">Blue arrow icon next to a shelf</dt>
          <dd class="text-sm">That shelf is set to sync to your Kobo. (See "The 'syncs' label" above.)</dd>
        </div>
      </div>
    </dl>
  </section>

  <%# Reading progress %>
  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-stone-900 mb-3">Reading progress</h2>
    <p class="text-stone-700 mb-3">
      Your Kobo reports back to Tsundoku every time it syncs. You'll see:
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1 text-stone-700">
      <li>An <strong>amber progress bar</strong> across the bottom of a cover for books you're partway through.</li>
      <li>A book disappears from the "currently reading" lens once it's marked finished.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-stone-700 mt-3">
      If you read a book on paper, you can mark it finished manually
      from the book's detail page.
    </p>
  </section>

  <%# Troubleshooting %>
  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-stone-900 mb-3">When something doesn't go as expected</h2>
    <dl class="space-y-4 text-stone-700">
      <div>
        <dt class="font-semibold text-stone-900">A book I downloaded from Shelfmark didn't show up.</dt>
        <dd class="text-sm mt-1">Give it two minutes — auto-ingest runs every two minutes. If it still doesn't appear, check the bell icon in the top-right; a red "ingest failed" task there will explain why.</dd>
      </div>

      <div>
        <dt class="font-semibold text-stone-900">A book is on my Kobo but doesn't show in "On your Kobo."</dt>
        <dd class="text-sm mt-1">The count shows books currently flagged for sync (via a syncing shelf or per-book toggle). If the book got onto the Kobo from an earlier sync but is no longer flagged, it'll stay on the device until the next sync removes it. Visit the book's detail page and re-enable <strong>Sync to device</strong>.</dd>
      </div>

      <div>
        <dt class="font-semibold text-stone-900">I clicked a "syncs" label and nothing happened.</dt>
        <dd class="text-sm mt-1">That's expected — "syncs" is a label, not a button. See <em>The "syncs" label isn't a button</em> above.</dd>
      </div>

      <div>
        <dt class="font-semibold text-stone-900">I wiped my Kobo and the books didn't come back on the next sync.</dt>
        <dd class="text-sm mt-1">
          When you delete books on the Kobo, the device tells Tsundoku
          which ones it removed, and Tsundoku automatically re-sends
          them on the next sync. If a book is still missing after two
          syncs, go to
          <%= link_to "Sync with Kobo", kobo_sync_path, class: "text-amber-700 underline hover:text-amber-800" %>
          (in the user menu) and click <strong>Force full re-sync</strong>
          — that's the manual escape hatch.
        </dd>
      </div>
    </dl>
  </section>
</div>
